data.notes: A GMAB guarantees minimum accumulation benefit on the Term End Date equal to the sum of (1) Purchase payments during the first 90 days of the term multiplied by the 100% GMAB factor: and (2) additional Purchase Payments during the Initial Term, multiplied by the applicable GMAB Subsequent Purchase Payment Adjustment Factor and GMAB Factor of 100%; as adjusted by partial withdrawals. The current GMAB Subsequent Purchase Payment Adjustment Factors for the initial Term are (50%: 6-3rd yrs, 60%: 2nd yr, 70%: 1st yr, 85%: 0th yr). For successive Terms, if elected, we guarantee the sum of (1) Contract Value on the Term Start Date multiplied by the applicable GMAB Factor; and (2) additional Purchase Payments during the Term, multiplied by the applicable GMAB Subsequent Purchase Payment Adjustment Factor and GMAB Factor, as adjusted by partial withdrawals and At the 7-year term end date if the contract value is less than the GMAB base, the GMAB credit will be added to restore it to the guaranteed contract value.

data.notes: A benefit provides a guaranteed market protection benefit at the end of the Term for an additional charge. On the 7-year Term End Date, the GMPB Credit to your Contract Value if the GMPB Base is higher than the Contract Value. The GMPB Credit is equal to the lesser of (1) the GMPB Base on the Term End Date minus the Contract Value on the Term End Date and (2) the GMPB Buffer on the Term End Date. The amount used to determine the GMPB credit on the term end date. The GMPB buffer is equal to the GMPB base on a term start date multiplied by a 10% GMPB buffer factor. The minimum GMPB Buffer Factor is 0% and the maximum GMPB Buffer Factor is 75%. The current cancellation thresholds for GMPB stand at 190% by the conclusion of the 7th year.

data.name: Income Boost GLWB
data.availRestrictionFxdAccount: Any allocation of Purchase Payments or transfer to Guaranteed Period Account other than DCA Program will terminate the rider.
data.availWhenAdded: No longer available for new purchases.
data.change: Once elected may not be changed.
data.effectChangeOwnership: Change in ownership will result in termination of rider.
data.gmwbCancellation: May be voluntarily terminated at any time. If elected in combination with GMPB rider, may be terminated on or after the 5th anniversary (Armor Flex 7 GMPB); or 7th anniversary (Armor Flex 10 GMPB).
data.gmwbTermination: The benefit will terminate immediately upon the occurrence of the earliest of:- 1) death, 2) annuitization, 3) termination of contract, 4) termination of GLWB, or 5) benefit base and contract value reduce to zero.
data.spousalContinuationOption: Surviving spouse may elect to continue benefit after death of owner under joint life option.
data.partialWithdrawals: Early Withdrawals could reduce Withdrawal Benefit Base by more than the dollar amount of the Early Withdrawals.
data.reqdMinDistributions: After the Income Start Date, the GLWB permits to withdraw RMD Amount each year without reducing Withdrawal Benefit Base.
data.benefitDescription: Rider provides a guaranteed stream of Income for the life of the owner and annuitant with an opportunity to increase with available Bonus and Annual Step-up.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The GLWB allows to withdraw a guaranteed amount of money each year, referred to as Annual Withdrawal Amount (AWA). AWA is determined by multiplying the Withdrawal Benefit Base by Lifetime Withdrawal Percentage as on the Income Start date. On the rider issue date Withdrawal Benefit Base will be equal to the initial Purchase Payment, thereafter increasing by any additional purchase payments and available Step-ups or Bonus. On each Contract Anniversary, greater of the 1) Step-up Value; or 2) Bonus Value will increase the Withdrawal Benefit Base.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: On each Contract Anniversary, prior to Income Start Date, Withdrawal Benefit Base is increased to the greatest of 1) the current Contract Value; or 2) the current Withdrawal Benefit Base plus any Bonus Amount available under the Bonus Feature, adjusted for any additional purchase payments, or early withdrawals.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: On each Contract Anniversary, after the Lifetime Income is elected, Withdrawal Benefit Base is increased to the greatest of 1) the current Contract Value; or 2) the current Withdrawal Benefit Base increased proportionally by any applicable Bonus Amount to reflect the days elapsed since the last Contract Anniversary. Following the Income Start Date, the Withdrawal Benefit Base will not decrease unless the cumulative withdrawals in the Contract Year exceed the AWA and Bonus Feature will no longer be available, however Step-up continues, until the valuation date, immediately preceding the Annuitization. Income Boost can step up on a Quarterly basis.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary, prior to the Income Start Date, if Highest Quarterly Contract Value for the Contract Year just ended is higher than the Withdrawal Benefit Base, then the Withdrawal Benefit Base will be stepped-up to equals to the Highest Quarterly Contract Value and the Bonus Period restarts with new Bonus Base equals to the stepped-up Withdrawal Benefit Base.
data.notes: May be elected in combination with an Armor Flex GMPB rider. Only one rider may be utilized.
data.withdrawalNotes: Lifetime Withdrawal Percentages are based on youngest covered person's age on the day of Early Withdrawals are available prior to turning on income under the GLWB.
data.chargeNotes: The current benefit Fee is 0.375% quarterly (1.50% annually) and maximum 0.625% quarterly (2.50% annually).

LWAF is equals to the difference between the Adjustment Election Rate and the Adjustment Base Rate, where Adjustment Rate is the average of the 10 Yr Treasury Rate and 30 Yr Treasury Rate on the last Business Day of the month (prior to the Election Date for Election Rate and prior to the Issue Date for Base Rate).
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: On each Contract Anniversary, prior to Income Start Date, Withdrawal Benefit Base is increased to the greatest of 1) the current Contract Value; or 2) the current Withdrawal Benefit Base plus any Bonus Amount available under the Bonus Feature, adjusted for any additional purchase payments, or early withdrawals.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: On each Contract Anniversary, after the Lifetime Income is elected, Withdrawal Benefit Base is increased to the greatest of 1) the current Contract Value; or 2) the current Withdrawal Benefit Base increased proportionally by any applicable Bonus Amount to reflect the days elapsed since the last Contract Anniversary. Following the Income Start Date, the Withdrawal Benefit Base will not decrease unless the cumulative withdrawals in the Contract Year exceed the AWA and Bonus Feature will no longer be available, however Step-up continues, until the valuation date, immediately preceding the Annuitization.
data.benefitBaseEnhanceStep: On each contract anniversary, if contract value is higher than the withdrawal benefit base plus any applicable bonus amount, the withdrawal benefit base will automatically increase to the contract value. If withdrawal benefit base is stepped up to contract value in the first 10 years, and prior to the income start date, bonus period will restart.
data.withdrawalNotes: Lifetime Withdrawal Percentages are based on youngest covered person's age on the day of first withdrawal.
data.chargeNotes: The current benefit Fee is 0.3375% quarterly (1.35% annually) and maximum 0.625% quarterly (2.50% annually) locked in for 2-year period at the rider election date.
data.feeOption: The annual GLWB Fee Rate increases, when a Step-Up occurs resulting in an increase to the Withdrawal Benefit Base, after the GLWB Fee Rate Lock Period, which is currently two years from the Election Date.
data.restrictionOnSubAcctNotes: Owner must allocate 100% of the account value to designated investment options.
